  "text": "## Apache Flink Windowing API Extension Points\n\n### 1. WindowAssigner Abstract Base Class\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/WindowAssigner.java\n\n**Class:** public abstract class WindowAssigner<T, W extends Window>\n\n**Abstract Methods (Extension Points):**\n- `Collection<W> assignWindows(T element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context)` - Assigns zero or more windows to an incoming element based on its timestamp\n- `Trigger<T, W> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns the default trigger associated with this assigner\n- `TypeSerializer<W> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Returns a serializer for the window type\n- `boolean isEventTime()` - Indicates whether windows are assigned based on event time or processing time\n\n**Inner Class:** WindowAssignerContext (abstract) with method `long getCurrentProcessingTime()`\n\n### 2. MergingWindowAssigner Subclass\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/MergingWindowAssigner.java\n\n**Class:** public abstract class MergingWindowAssigner<T, W extends Window> extends WindowAssigner<T, W>\n\n**Additional Abstract Method:**\n- `void mergeWindows(Collection<W> windows, MergeCallback<W> callback)` - Determines which windows should be merged and invokes the callback\n\n**Inner Interface:** MergeCallback<W> with method `void merge(Collection<W> toBeMerged, W mergeResult)`\n\n### 3. Trigger Base Class\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/triggers/Trigger.java\n\n**Class:** public abstract class Trigger<T, W extends Window> implements Serializable\n\n**Lifecycle Methods:**\n- `TriggerResult onElement(T element, long timestamp, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when an element arrives in a pane\n- `TriggerResult onProcessingTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when a processing-time timer fires\n- `TriggerResult onEventTime(long time, W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Called when an event-time timer fires\n- `void onMerge(W window, OnMergeContext ctx)` - Called when windows merge (optional, only if canMerge() returns true)\n- `void clear(W window, TriggerContext ctx)` - Clears state for a window before it is purged\n- `boolean canMerge()` - Returns true if trigger supports state merging (default: false)\n\n**Inner Interface:** TriggerContext with methods for timer management and state access\n\n**Inner Interface:** OnMergeContext extends TriggerContext with `void mergePartitionedState(StateDescriptor<S, ?> stateDescriptor)`\n\n### 4. EventTimeSessionWindows Reference Implementation\n**Location:** flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/assigners/EventTimeSessionWindows.java\n\n**Class:** public class EventTimeSessionWindows extends MergingWindowAssigner<Object, TimeWindow>\n\n**Implementation of assignWindows():**\n```java\npublic Collection<TimeWindow> assignWindows(\n    Object element, long timestamp, WindowAssignerContext context) {\n    return Collections.singletonList(new TimeWindow(timestamp, timestamp + sessionTimeout));\n}\n```\nCreates a single window for each element spanning from the element's timestamp to timestamp + session timeout.\n\n**Implementation of mergeWindows():**\n```java\npublic void mergeWindows(\n    Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c) {\n    TimeWindow.mergeWindows(windows, c);\n}\n```\nDelegates to the static utility method in TimeWindow class which merges overlapping windows.\n\n**Other Methods:**\n- `Trigger<Object, TimeWindow> getDefaultTrigger()` - Returns EventTimeTrigger.create()\n- `TypeSerializer<TimeWindow> getWindowSerializer(ExecutionConfig executionConfig)` - Returns new TimeWindow.Serializer()\n- `boolean isEventTime()` - Returns true\n- Static factory: `EventTimeSessionWindows withGap(Duration size)`\n- Static factory: `<T> DynamicEventTimeSessionWindows<T> withDynamicGap(SessionWindowTimeGapExtractor<T> extractor)`\n\n### 5. TimeWindow Class\n**Location:** flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java\n\n**Class:** public class TimeWindow extends Window\n\n**Constructor:**\n- `TimeWindow(long start, long end)` - Creates a window from start (inclusive) to end (exclusive)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `long getStart()` - Returns the start timestamp\n- `long getEnd()` - Returns the end timestamp (exclusive)\n- `long maxTimestamp()` - Returns end - 1 (largest timestamp that belongs to window)\n- `boolean intersects(TimeWindow other)` - Checks if windows overlap\n- `TimeWindow cover(TimeWindow other)` - Returns the minimal window covering both windows\n- `boolean equals(Object o)` and `int hashCode()` - Equality comparison\n\n**Static Utilities:**\n- `void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Merges overlapping TimeWindow instances\n- `long getWindowStartWithOffset(long timestamp, long offset, long windowSize)` - Computes window start time\n\n**Inner Class:** Serializer extends TypeSerializerSingleton<TimeWindow>\n\n## Summary of Extension Points\n\nDevelopers implementing custom window assigners must:\n1. Extend `WindowAssigner<T, W>` and implement: assignWindows(), getDefaultTrigger(), getWindowSerializer(), isEventTime()\n2. For merging windows, extend `MergingWindowAssigner<T, W>` and additionally implement: mergeWindows()\n3. Implement a `Trigger<T, W>` subclass with: onElement(), onProcessingTime(), onEventTime(), clear()\n4. For merging triggers, override canMerge() to return true and implement onMerge()\n5. Typically use `TimeWindow` as the window type, which handles window merging through its static utility method"
